text: Hey, can't remember if I found this from one of you guys or online, but wanted to share: <http://www.typetester.org/>

attachments.text: The Typetester is an online application for comparison of the fonts for the screen. Its primary role is to make web designer’s life easier.
attachments.fallback: The Typetester is an online application for comparison of the fonts for the screen. Its primary role is to make web designer’s life easier.

text: It lets you render default web fonts and even any font on your machine, in a website instantly. And it lets you adjust all the little things like size and spacing, etc.
Potentially useful tool. I'd be curious to hear what <@U02618EV1> thinks about it.
